            <title><![CDATA[Trump's limits are tested after some Republicans push back]]></title>
            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/trumps-limits-are-tested-after-some-republicans-push-back</link>
            <description><![CDATA[The Senate is in the midst of voting on $72 billion of funding for Immigration and Customs Enforcement as well as the Department of Homeland Security. The package has been held up for months with amendment votes expected to run well into the night. But it's still unclear whether Republican leaders will ultimately be able to wrangle enough votes to pass the measure. Lisa Desjardins has the latest.]]></description>
